By res extra patrimonium seems to be meant a thing which is legally incapable of being owned by a private person, i.e. it does not cease to be in patrimonio by not having, or by ceasing to have, a private owner. Extra patrimonium is thus equivalent to extra commercium: but· in the former the res -is viewed as incapable of private dominium, in the latter rather as incapable of acquisition by a private person.
